		<h5 class="underline">Links Setup</h5>
		<ol class="flow-text">
			<li>Click <a href="settings.html" target="_blank">here</a> to go to Settings</li>
			<li>Scroll down to the tab that says <em>Settings</em> and press it </li>
			<li>Next, open up your First Block Teacher's Website. Copy the link from the address bar.</li>
			<li>Go back to the PlanVIEW Settings page and  paste the link in the box that says <em>1st Block Website Link</em></li>
			<li>Do it this for the rest of your classes.</li>
			<li>Click Save. You should get message that says Settings Saved </li>
		</ol>
		<blockquote>
			<p class="flow-text"><strong>Important Note</strong></p>
			<p class="flow-text">If your class doesn't have a website or you do not use the website, you MUST still put a link of a website in that box. It can be important websites you visit or something like google.com.</p>
		</blockquote>
		<p class="flow-text">Now, if you ever have to go to your teacher's website quickly then you can click (menu) button and then the  tab you need instead of searching for it on your browser</p>
