		<p class="flow-text">Taking quick notes on your phone of values from a lab or homework your teacher assigns can be extremely useful. With the PlanVIEW app, you can take quick notes very simply. Hereâ€™s how</p>
		<ol class="flow-text">
			<li>Click the line on the box of the block you want to type a note for.</li>
			<li>Type up your note</li>
			<li>Click Save Note </li>
		</ol>
		<p class="flow-text">Your note is now <strong>saved </strong> and will be <strong>available</strong> when you open your app.</p>
		<blockquote>
			<strong class="flow-text">Important Note</strong>
			<p class="flow-text">If you have a long note (ex. paragraphs) then you can still save it. Type or copy and paste what you need and then click save. When viewing the note, click on the paragraph and then press enter on your keyboard. The note will expand in a scrollable view</p>
